positive psychology the pursuit of happiness positive psychology the pursuit of happiness facebook twitter email print add to calendar this 5 week workshop will explore the new strength based approach to positive psychology aka happiness we will discuss research on happiness for the purpose of developing improved personal well being each class will include guided practice discussion and personal reflection texts for the class are awakening joy 10 steps that will put you on the road to real happiness by james baraz and shoshana alexander and stress free for good 10 scientifically proven life skills for health and happiness by fred luskin and kenneth pelletier books are not included in class fee instructor frederic luskin phd director of the stanford university forgiveness project when tuesday october 5 2010 7 00 pm approximate duration of 1.5 hour s where 1101 welch road building a suite 6 map audience faculty staff alumni friends general public members tags class humanities health wellness sponsor health improvement program contact 650 721 6003 ausserer stanford edu admission 5 tuesday evening classes register at hip stanford edu class fee $236 class code ppph 01 stap ea funds approved last modified october 5 2010
